CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 16, 1953, pg. 14, reads: "Given Violin - Arlene Rogers, left, views smilingly the violin case and bow which were given to her Tuesday night by an 'anonymous friend' through Frontiers Club. Arleen [sic], selected to play with the Pittsburgh Symphony, was guest artist for the Frontiers. She was accompanied by 11-year-old Patricia Prattis, right. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Arlene Rogers and Patricia Prattis (Jennings) posed with violin at Frontiers Club meeting
